title: ArchiCAD-12-KOR-BIM-Interactive-Training-Guide-Windows.exe
description:
Korean ArchiCAD Tutorial:

In this Interactive Training Guide you will be provided with step by step instructions to build the Massaro House, using ArchiCAD's  BIM  architectural environment, also known as the Virtual Building concept. Frank Lloyd Wright designed this project to accentuate a specific New York island in 1950. The Massaros ran the plans by a Frank Lloyd Wright expert architect, Thomas A. Heinz, AIA, who used ArchiCAD to create the construction documentation based on Wright's 5 original pencil drawings. This interactive tutorial is intended to support your early ArchiCAD experiences.
